    SIG SAUER P238 (.380 ACP)
    =========================
    Scaled-down 1911 with crisp SAO trigger in pocket-pistol form
    
    Real-World Specs:
    - Barrel: 2.7" (shorter than PPK)
    - Weight: 15.2 oz empty (3.8 oz lighter than PPK)
    - Capacity: 6+1 (7+1 extended)
    - Muzzle Velocity: 850-950 fps (90gr)
    - Muzzle Energy: 170-200 ft-lbs
    - SAO Trigger: 7-8 lb crisp break
    - Production: 2009-discontinued
    - MSRP: $300-700 (secondary market)
    
    Ballistic Notes:
    - Shorter barrel = slightly less velocity than PPK
    - Locked-breech action = milder felt recoil
    - 1911-style = every shot identical trigger feel
    - Manual safety required (cocked-and-locked carry)
    
    Game Balance:
    - Damage: 18 (slightly less than PPK due to barrel)
    - 6 shots close, 11-12 at range
    - Better accuracy than PPK (SAO vs heavy DA)
    - Lower recoil (locked breech + lighter weight)
-->
